 &lt;p&gt;Seeraga Samba/ Jeeraga Samba is popularly known as &lt;strong&gt;Biryani rice&lt;/strong&gt; as it is most commonly used in South Indian Biryani varieties. Since it resembles like Seeragam (cumin), hence the name Seeraga samba.&lt;/p&gt;
